libxcb
------------------------------------------
libxcb provides an interface to the X Window System protocol, which replaces
the current Xlib interface. It has several advantages over Xlib, including:
- size: small library and lower memory footprint
- latency hiding: batch several requests and wait for the replies later
- direct protocol access: one-to-one mapping between interface and protocol
- proven thread support: transparently access XCB from multiple threads
- easy extension implementation: interfaces auto-generated from XML-XCB

Xlib can also use XCB as a transport layer, allowing software to make
requests and receive responses with both, which eases porting to XCB.
However, client programs, libraries, and toolkits will gain the most
benefit from a native XCB port.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-15
  libXau6-1.0.4-1
  libXdmcp6-1.0.2-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.63-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-2
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.4.2-1
  gawk-3.1.6-1
  libpthread-stubs-0.1-1
  libxslt-1.1.24-2
  make-3.81-1
  pkg-config-0.23a-2
  sed-4.1.5-2
  xcb-proto-1.2-1

Canonical website:
  http://xcb.freedesktop.org/

Canonical download:
  http://xcb.freedesktop.org/dist/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libxcb-<VER>-<REL>-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libxcb-<VER>-<REL>.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libxcb-<VER>-<REL>-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-<VER>-<REL>.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-composite-devel-<VER>-<REL>.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-composite0-<VER>-<REL>.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-damage-devel-<VER>-<REL>.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-damage0-<VER>-<REL>.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-devel-<VER>-<REL>.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-doc-<VER>-<REL>.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-dpms-devel-<VER>-<REL>.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-dpms0-<VER>-<REL>.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-glx-devel-<VER>-<REL>.tar.bz2
